         <listPerson>
            <person xml:id="pers1038">
               <p>A native of <placeName>Halifax, Yorkshire</placeName>, Hodgson became active in
                  the Methodist society in <date when="1775">1775</date>. He underwent an
                  evangelical conversion in <date when="1777">1777</date> and began to exhort
                  locally. In <date when="1780">1780</date> he was accepted on trial into the <seg
                     ana="itinerancy">itinerant</seg> ministry (see <hi rend="italic">Works</hi>,
                  10:496). He continued to serve until his death, by drowning, while crossing the
                  river <placeName>Were</placeName>. See Atmore, <hi rend="italic">Memorial</hi>,
                  191–99; and <hi rend="italic">Minutes</hi> (post-Wesley, <date when="1795"
                     >1795</date>), 1:318.</p>
            </person>
         </listPerson>
      </body>
